Vue js is a progressive frontend framework, you need a separate application for backend developed in server side frameworks like (node js, expressjs, hapijs, sailsjs, loopbackjs, php..etc)

    &quot;scripts&quot;: {
        &quot;serve&quot;: &quot;vue-cli-service serve&quot;,
        &quot;build&quot;: &quot;vue-cli-service build&quot;,
        &quot;lint&quot;: &quot;vue-cli-service lint&quot;
      }

from the above scripts, if you use 

    npm run build

It creates a static `js`, `cs`, `html` file. You don&#39;t require any application server to run vue application. Webpack loads the Complete vue application to a static application. You can just place those files in a Web server like Nginx or using Github pages free hosting to host the site

In the development phase, it internally uses a application server on running `npm run server` to lift the application

